1. For troubleshooting customers like CIT that are using their company ID verification and Single-Sign On (SSO) to access ActiveDisclosure, the only setting that needs to be checked and potentially updated is &#39;Username&#39; in the &#39;Account User&#39; section of the Admin Console.  If the &#39;Username&#39; matches the &#39;Contact Email&#39; then there is nothing else we can to do on our side.  Any customer who still has login difficulties should then talk with their company admin or IT staff to see if they have the correct permissions to access ActiveDisclosure within their corporate domain.
2. To verify &#39;Username&#39; equals &#39;Contact email&#39; for users, open the CLAMP site and log in with your AD3 credentials.
  1. [https://portal.activedisclosure.com/Portal/](https://portal.activedisclosure.com/Portal/)
3. Once logged in, you will see the Home Screen below:

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. To check and possibly update the user(s), navigate to the existing Account
  1. Click on &quot;Admin Console&quot;

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1.
  1. Enter the company name and click Enter

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1.
  1. Click on the arrow next to the account name to navigate to the Account Details

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1.
  1. The Username for the users in the account will need to be checked on this screen.  If any do not have the company email (like first.last@companyname.com) as the Username, they will need to be edited manually.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1.
  1. To edit, click the three dots at the right edge of the user line, then click &quot;Edit&quot; in the drop-down box.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1.
  1. Edit the users &#39;Username&#39; to match &#39;Contact email&#39; like this:

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1.
  1.
    1. **Note:** The Username field was originally formatted to be like &#39;first.last@activedisclosure.com&#39; for pre-existing accounts.
  2. Verify the information has been entered correctly, then:
    1. Click &quot;OK&quot;, you should see the following screen:

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1.
  1. Edit any of the other users in the same way if necessary.
